# Drawer

IDS Drawers use a modal state to focus the user’s attention on a key action or flow.
They are supplementary surfaces used alongside the main content. They appear only
from the page margins displaying content that lives off the edge of the screen.

IDS Drawers block content and are intended as a temporary workspace.

## Installation & Import

```bash
yarn add @ids-ts/drawer
```

```tsx
import {
  Drawer,
  DrawerContent,
  DrawerHeader,
  DrawerSearchHeader,
  DrawerFooter,
  DrawerMenuIcon,
} from '@ids-ts/drawer';
```

